 His non-scientific works include: About Zionism: Speeches and Lectures by Professor Albert Einstein (1930), &lt;U+201C&gt;Why War?&lt;U+201D&gt; (1933, co-authored by Sigmund Freud), The World As I See It (1934), Out of My Later Years (1950), and a book on science for the general reader, The Evolution of Physics (1938, co-authored by Leopold Infeld).↩
